parameter $useimap has been deprecated - meaning: do not use, will be removed in a future version.
The parameter could have a bool value before. 

Now a true or false value will trigger an error and code that worked with a previous phpMailer version will no longer work. However if you leave out the parameter or set it to null then the same code will no longer work with older phpMailer versions that still accepted the boolean version.

This is not a deprecation warning. This is creating an incompatibillity. Applications that share an interface module to phpMailer cannot be migrated individually to a newer phpMailer versions without breaking either the Applications with the old or new phpMailer version.

